      <subsection xml:id="electricity-resistors">
         <title>Resistors</title>
         <p>Resistors are made of materials that conduct electricity, but offer opposition to current flow.  They limit the flow of current, and can be used for various purposes, including voltage division and current limiting.</p>
         <figure xml:id="fig_resistors">
            <caption>Carbon resistors, potentiometer, surface mount reistors</caption>
